# Response Control & Space Programming Error Handling

You are strictly required to follow the "Space Programming" mindset. We treat errors as values, NOT exceptions.

## 1. The Ultimate Response Types
All core functions, Use Cases, and Controllers MUST return `CommonResponse<TBody, TError>`.
DO NOT use `throw new Error()` or NestJS HTTP Exceptions inside Use Cases. Return an `ErrorResponse` instead.

Success payloads exposed to HTTP MUST be Response DTOs (after `Mapper.toResponse(domain)`), not raw domain entities nor Prisma models. See `docs/specs/security/02-sanitize-response/README.md`.

Assume the following types are globally available or imported from `@shared/types/response.type.ts`:

```typescript
declare const __brand: unique symbol;
export type Brand<K, T> = K & { [__brand]: T };
export type StatusCode = Brand<number, 'StatusCode'>;

export interface BaseResponse {
  status: StatusCode;
  timestamp: string;
  traceId: string;
}

export type SuccessResponse<TBody> = BaseResponse & {
  success: true;
  message: 'success';
  body: TBody;
  error?: never;
};

export type ErrorResponse<TError = unknown> = BaseResponse & {
  success: false;
  message: string;
  body?: never;
  error: TError;
};

export type CommonResponse<TBody, TError = unknown> =
  | SuccessResponse<TBody>
  | ErrorResponse<TError>;
```

### 2. Domain-Specific Error Constants
Every module MUST have an error.const.ts file to define its specific error codes and messages. Magic numbers or hardcoded error strings are STRICTLY FORBIDDEN.

File Location: src/modules/[module-name]/constants/[module-name]-error.const.ts

```TypeScript
// Example: player-error.const.ts
import { createStatusCode } from '@shared/utils/response.util';

export const PLAYER_ERRORS = {
  NOT_FOUND: {
    status: createStatusCode(404),
    code: 'PLAYER_1001',
    message: 'Player data not found in the system.',
  },
  INSUFFICIENT_FUNDS: {
    status: createStatusCode(400),
    code: 'PLAYER_1002',
    message: 'Insufficient Pang Coins for this transaction.',
  },
} as const;
```

### 3. Use Case Implementation Rules
Use Cases must return `Promise<CommonResponse<TResponseDto, TError>>` for success bodies.
Do NOT throw exceptions for business logic failures.

```TypeScript
// Correct Use Case Example:
@Injectable()
export class DeductPangCoinUseCase {
  constructor(
    @Inject('IPlayerRepository') private readonly playerRepo: IPlayerRepository,
    private readonly cls: ClsService,
  ) {}

  async execute(
    playerId: PlayerId,
    amount: number,
  ): Promise<CommonResponse<PlayerResponseDto, string>> {
    const traceId = this.cls.get<string>('x-request-id');
    const player = await this.playerRepo.findById(playerId);

    if (!player) {
      return {
        success: false,
        status: PLAYER_ERRORS.NOT_FOUND.status,
        message: PLAYER_ERRORS.NOT_FOUND.message,
        error: PLAYER_ERRORS.NOT_FOUND.code,
        timestamp: new Date().toISOString(),
        traceId,
      };
    }

    if (player.pangCoin < amount) {
      return {
        success: false,
        status: PLAYER_ERRORS.INSUFFICIENT_FUNDS.status,
        message: PLAYER_ERRORS.INSUFFICIENT_FUNDS.message,
        error: PLAYER_ERRORS.INSUFFICIENT_FUNDS.code,
        timestamp: new Date().toISOString(),
        traceId,
      };
    }

    player.deductCoins(amount);
    await this.playerRepo.save(player);

    return {
      success: true,
      status: createStatusCode(200),
      message: 'success',
      body: PlayerMapper.toResponse(player),
      timestamp: new Date().toISOString(),
      traceId,
    };
  }
}
```

### 4. Controller Implementation Rules
Controllers must act as a pass-through for the CommonResponse. Trace ID is created by Context Middleware from `x-request-id` and read from CLS inside Use Cases.

```typescript
// Correct Controller Example:
@Controller('admin/players')
export class AdminPlayerController {
  constructor(private readonly deductPangCoinUseCase: DeductPangCoinUseCase) {}

  @Post(':id/deduct')
  async deductCoins(
    @Param('id') id: PlayerId,
    @Body() dto: DeductCoinDto,
  ): Promise<CommonResponse<PlayerResponseDto, string>> {
    return this.deductPangCoinUseCase.execute(id, dto.amount);
  }
}
```
